definition.value: An N-{1-[(naphthalen-2-yl)amino]-1-oxo-3-phenylpropan-2-yl}benzamide that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzoyl-D-phenylalanine with the amino group of 2-aminonaphthalene.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of D- and L-N-benzoylarginine 2-naphthylamide.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 12 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 16 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 22 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 24 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 24 with 1 double bond.
A member of the class of N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamides that is 5-carbamimidamido-N-(naphthalen-2-yl)pentanamide in which one of the hydrogens at position 2 has been replaced by a benzamido group.

An N-{1-[(naphthalen-2-yl)amino]-1-oxo-3-phenylpropan-2-yl}benzamide that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzoyl-D-arginine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.
A mixture that is the black porous residue, consisting of carbon and any remaining ash, obtained by pyrolysis of animal or vegetable matter in a limited supply of air.
A mamber of the class of benzaldehydes carrying a dimethylamino substituent at position 4. Used as an indicator for detection of indoles and hydrazine.
An alpha-D-galactoside having a 4-methylumbelliferyl substituent at the anomeric position
A beta-D-galactoside having a 4-methylumbelliferyl substituent at the anomeric position.
A beta-D-glucoside having a 4-methylumbelliferyl substituent at the anomeric position.
A member of the class of coumarins that is 4-methylumbelliferone in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a butyryl group.
An alpha-D-glucoside that is beta-D-glucopyranose in which the anomeric hydroxy hydrogen is replaced by a 4-nitrophenyl group.
A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 3'-monophosphate that is the mono-(5-bromo-4-chloro-indol-3-yl) ester of thymidine 3'-phosphate.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 3-acetylchlorophyll a.
A chlorophyll that is the ester obtained by formal condensation between the carboxy group of bacteriochlorophyllide a and the hydroxy group of geranylgeraniol.
An epoxycarotenol that beta-cryptoxanthin in which the 5,6-double bond has been epoxidised.
A 1-alkylglycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl group is specified as octadecyl.
A N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the acyl group specified is (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.
A member of the class of beta-carbolines that is 1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-beta-carboline substituted at position 3 by a carboxy group.
A epoxycarotenol that is capsanthin in which the 5,6-double bond has been epoxidised.
A monohydroxybenzoic acid that is 2-hydroxybenzoic acid in which the hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a beta-D-xylosyloxy group.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 20 carbons and 5 double bonds.
A guaiacyl lignin that is guaiacylglycerol in which the hydrogen on the 2-hydroxy function has been replaced by a beta-coniferyl group.
A guaiacyl lignin that is guaiacylglycerol in which the hydrogen on the 2-hydroxy function has been replaced by a 4-(1,2,3-trihydroxypropan-1-yl)-2,6-dimethoxyphenyl group.
A guaiacyl lignin obtained by cyclodimerisation of coniferol.
A guaiacyl lignin that is medioresinol in which one of the phenolic hydrogens is replaced by a guaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is scopoletin in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a guaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin obtained by formal cyclocodensation between guaiacylglycerol and esculetin. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is ferulic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfoguaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is ferulic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfoguaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is glycosmisic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfo group.
A guaiacyl lignin that is glycosmisic acid in which the alcoholic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfo group.
A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine obtained by formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of azelaic acid with the 1-hydroxy group of sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine obtained by formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of azelaic acid with the 1-hydroxy group of sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.
A carotenoid ether that is spheroidene substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group.
A carotenoid ether that is spheroidene carrying two hydroxy groups, both at position 2.
An amidobenzoic acid obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of [(4-methylbenzene-1-sulfonyl)oxy]acetic acid with the amino group of 4-amino-2-hydroxybenzoic acid.
A sulfur-containing amino acid that is the sulfoxide obtained by formal oxygenation of the sulfur atom of pentahomomethionine.
A sulfur-containing amino acid that is the sulfoxide obtained by formal oxygenation of the sulfur atom of hexahomomethionine.
A carotenoid ether that is spirilloxanthin substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group.
A carotenoid ether that is spirilloxanthin carrying two hydroxy groups, both at position 2.
A carotenoid ether that is spirilloxanthin substituted at positions 2  and 2' by oxo and hydroxy groups respectively.
A carotenoid ether that is spirilloxanthin carrying an oxo group at position 2 as well as two hydroxy group, both at position 2'.
An ammonium salt consisting of ammonium and oxalate ions in a 2:1 ratio.
